Notice the pattern:

- builtins live in shared runtime code
- the JIT cooperates with them through stubs and VM-aware calls

That is the right direction for a small engine.

## The Main Lesson

Native builtins are not an escape hatch that makes VM design irrelevant.

They are part of the VM design.

They let the engine centralize complicated behavior in one place while the JIT focuses on speeding up the execution path around that behavior.

